casebody.data:
RECONSIDERATION DOCKET

96-1039. Bank One, Columbus, N.A. v. O’Brien.

Franklin County, No. 95APD08-1094. Reported at 75 Ohio St.3d 1486, 664 N.E.2d 538. On June 10,1996, appellant filed a document titled “Motion to Reinstate Appeal.”

It is determined by the court that appellant’s motion is, in essence, a motion for reconsideration of this court’s entry of May 15,1996, and, as such, is untimely. Accordingly,

IT IS ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that appellant’s motion to reinstate appeal be, and hereby is, stricken.
